The host is 
<taxonomicName box="[773,961,1810,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Lygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineolaris">
<emphasis box="[773,961,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lygus lineolaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species must be bivoltine as 
<specimenCount box="[304,473,1850,1876]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
was collected from a nymph in mid­June from the first nymphal
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">generation and a second specimen was collected from a nymph in late July from the second nymphal generation.</paragraph>
